<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>DDB0105</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">R N Lawton – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 65.2pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Draft Deregulation Bill and Rights of Way</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">The Ridgeway and Sugar Way </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">–</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> Aldbourne</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">I write in relation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt"> to your deliberations on off road motor vehicles and motor cycles use of BOATS and similar rights of way.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">Here in the Marlborough downs a.o.n.b we are blessed with many lovely green lanes which used to be havens of peace and tranquillity, where walkers and horse riders could enjoy the lovely springy turf. NO LONGER IS THIS POSSIBLE!</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">This is due to the mindless use of off road vehicles which have made them impassable to walkers and riders alike due to the creation of massively deep ruts and mud. It goes without saying the noise and danger created is considerable. We have seen in excess of 25 4x4’s nose to tail in pouring rain enjoying the destruction of our own land.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">The natural reaction to this damage from Councils is to pave the track. This has created other, possibly more, disturbing phenomena; these paved tracks have given access to criminals who now use them to break into our farms and houses as well as criminal damage from joy riding, hare coursing and poaching.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">The situation is becoming very serious</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> I urge the government to restrict the use of these tracks to non motorised traffic</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">14 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span